title: Bug 109350 - Output parameter not displaying in data set dialog
OB: When calling a stored procedure from Oracle database, the query result stored in an output parameter is not being displayed in the edit data set dialog.
EB: The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
SR:
1. Call a stored procedure from Oracle database.
2. Store the query result in an output parameter.
3. Open the edit data set dialog.
4. Verify that the output parameter is displayed in the dialog.
